Latin Interpretations of Ptolemy's Geographia

O. A. W. DILKE

Oves a thousand years after Ptolemy’s death, the Greek scholar Maximus Planudes, at the monastery of Chora, Constantinople,

But Planudes knew that Greeks, Romans and Arabs had used the Geogmfflzy, and that it had been accompanied by maps.
